A former Minister of Water Resources, Mrs Sarah Ochekpe has been sent to prison.  Ochekpe was sentenced to three months imprisonment by the Federal High Court sitting in Jos, the Plateau State capital. The court also sentenced a former Deputy Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the state, Raymond Dabo, and Evangelist Leo Sunday Jitung to three months imprisonment. The judgment was delivered by Justice Musa Kurna on Tuesday. Recall that the three had been standing trial for the past four years on charges bordering on conspiracy and money laundering. However, the sentence has an option of a fine of N1 million.  source JOS (Sundiata Post) - A Federal High Court sitting in Jos the Plateau State capital on Monday arraigned a former  Minister of Water Resources, Mrs. Sarah Reng Ochekpe, Former  Acting Chairman, Plateau state chapter of Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), Raymond Dabo and Plateau State campaign coordinator of 2015 Goodluck Jonathan,… In "Local News" A former Minister of Water Resources, Mrs. Sarah Ochekpe; former Chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party in Plateau State,  Mr. Raymond Dabo and the Coordinator of Jonathan/Sambo reelection campaign in Plateau State, Evangelist Lyons Sunday Jatau, will on February 13 know whether they will be committed to prison for allegedly… In "Local News" •Orji Uzor Kalu By Fasanmi Abiola  Here is a list of some former governors who have been successfully tried for corruption and jailed. James Bala Ngilari Ngilari, a former governor of Adamawa State was sentenced to 5 years in Jail in 2017 with no option in fine for awarding contract… In "News"